---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy · thelnk" description="How thelnk.is handles your data.">
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p class="lead">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      When you shorten a URL or upload a file, we store the metadata needed to operate the service (for example
      destination URL, file name, size, MIME type, and timestamps) in our database. Short links and file links are
      associated with your Clerk account when you are signed in, or stored without an account when you use the site
      anonymously.
    </p>

    <h2>Authentication</h2>
    <p>
      Sign-in and account management are provided by <a href="https://clerk.com/">Clerk</a>. Clerk’s privacy policy
      governs the data they process on our behalf for authentication.
    </p>

    <h2>Payments</h2>
    <p>
      If you purchase a <strong>lifetime</strong> license or subscribe to <strong>Pro monthly</strong>, payment processing is handled by <a href="https://stripe.com/">Stripe</a>.
      We do not store your full card number on our servers. Stripe’s privacy policy applies to payment data they
      collect.
    </p>

    <h2>Hosting and logs</h2>
    <p>
      The service runs on <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/">Cloudflare</a> (Workers, D1, R2, and related
      products). Cloudflare may process IP addresses and technical data as part of delivering and securing the site.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy questions, contact the operator of thelnk.is at the support channel you were given at purchase.</p>

    <p><a href="/">← Home</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 40rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .legal .lead { margin: 0 0 2rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .legal a { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
